The paper proposes a method for regularizing deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The experiments focus on tasks such as image classification, caption generation, and speech recognition, which are typically associated with computer vision, natural language processing, and speech processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves pruning and retraining networks, which are techniques commonly used in optimization and neural network compression, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves increasing model capacity, which is a topic related to neural architecture search and design, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
